This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with monocular depth estimation, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (DCNNs) also suggests that it falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The fact that the proposed method is designed for robotics applications, as mentioned in the abstract, makes the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category a likely candidate as well. Finally, the mention of benchmarks such as NYU Depth V2 and Make3D suggests that this paper could also be relevant to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CVPR) sub-category.
